ZH: 他听了那个坏消息，面不改色。
EN: He heard the bad news without any change of expression.

ZH: 她被批评了一番，仍然面不改色。
EN: She was criticized but remained expressionless.

ZH: 在比赛中，他面不改色地接受了失败。
EN: In the competition, he accepted the failure without any change of expression.

ZH: 他解释了很多次，但他的父母仍然面不改色地不理解他。
EN: He explained multiple times, but his parents remained expressionless and didn't understand him.

ZH: 当听到那个可怕的故事时，孩子们面不改色。
EN: The children remained expressionless when they heard the terrifying story.

